=Definition=

Aram Bartholl:

"Offline network operate outside the Internet. Such networks could range from artistic projects (eg. deadrops or wifitagger) and "personal networks" (eg PirateBox.cc or subnod.es), to community networks (eg commotionwireless.net, nethood) and large city-scale mesh networks (eg. guifi.net, freifunk.net, awmn.net.)."
(http://transmediale.de/content/offline-networks-unite)


=Status=

Aram Bartholl:

"The first assembly of off.networks took place at the CCC last month. In their second scheduled meeting during transmediale Festival, the members of this network wish to make their first effort to build a diverse and dynamic community around the design, implementation and deployment of offline networks in different contexts."
(http://transmediale.de/content/offline-networks-unite)

